page.title: 19Wetwang,Aeroplanes.
page.content:
Over Wetwang{planes}pass quite often.Some planes are agricultural and some are RAF planes.They both fly low over barns.They make a noise but they don't disturb people too much.
The{agricultural planes}come from spring till autumn.Sprayers are often helicopters . Sometimes they can be sued for spraying extra fields by accident.They always come low to spray. { RAF planes }come from the air field at Leconfield. They come all year round.These planes go very low. They make an interference on the television and radio but sometimes they fly high above the clouds.A couple pass over each day. {RAF planes}make more noise than {sprayers}because they have bigger engines.
